<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFF8FFEFD3D3F7620832D175" blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD3D3F7620F1DD10D" authority="Breddin, 1906" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1906" box="[199,809,773,798]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="torridus" variety="moestissimus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD3D3F7620D9CD10E" box="[199,424,773,797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD2F1F7610E4DD10E" box="[485,633,774,797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">moestissimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFF8FFEFD197F7620F1DD10D" author="Breddin" box="[643,809,773,798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Breddin, G. (1906) Rhynchotographische Beitrage. (Zweites Stuck.) Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 25 (5 - 7), 188 - 200." type="journal article" year="1906">
Breddin, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD1FAF7620F1DD10D" box="[750,809,773,798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD023F7610F93D10D" box="[823,935,774,798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Lectotype</typeStatus>
(present designation): ♀, [a small dark red square without text], “St. 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD2A1F74E0E10D151" box="[437,548,809,834]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Mopaliidae" genus="Catharina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Catharina</taxonomicName>
” [hw], “coll. \ Breddin”. Pinned, both antennae, left fore tarsus, segments II–III of right fore tarsus, and left hind leg lacking; deposited in 
<collectionCode id="ED440AF8FFF8FFEFD036F7290F54D175" box="[802,864,846,870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">SDEI</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation id="136E8EB8FFF8FFEFD064F72A0FCED175" box="[880,1018,845,870]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[172,1400,293,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,265,1869]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Lectotypes of Pachycoris torridus var. laetissimus Breddin, 1906 (Figs. 7 – 9) and var. moestissimus Breddin, 1906 (Figs. 10 – 12) and their labels. Figs. 7 and 10, dorsal view; Figs. 8 and 11, lateral view; Figs. 9 and 12, labels. Scales in mm. © SDEI." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264947/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
Figs. 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD0BBF7290FCED175" box="[943,1018,846,870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34FC1B6FFF8FFEFD3D3F7160880D449" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFF8FFEFD3D3F716088FD705" blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD3D3F7160D78D199" bold="true" box="[199,332,881,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Discussion.</emphasis>
Two varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD102F7150EBAD19A" box="[534,654,881,905]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD102F7150EBAD19A" box="[534,654,881,905]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFF8FFEFD07BF716082BD199" author="Breddin" box="[879,1055,881,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Breddin, G. (1906) Rhynchotographische Beitrage. (Zweites Stuck.) Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 25 (5 - 7), 188 - 200." type="journal article" year="1906">
Breddin (
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD0CEF7160823D199" box="[986,1047,881,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1906.0">1906</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Both names were proposed with incorrect gender ending; since they are combined with the masculine generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD758F7F209ACD1BD" authority="Burmeister, 1835" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[1100,1432,917,942]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD758F7F208FED1BE" box="[1100,1226,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris</emphasis>
Burmeister, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD649F7F209ACD1BD" box="[1373,1432,917,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1835.0">1835</number>
</taxonomicName>
, their gender ending is hereby changed to masculine following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFF8FFEFD05BF7DD084CD1C1" author="ICZN" box="[847,1144,953,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode id="ED440AF8FFF8FFEFD05BF7DD0FA4D1C1" box="[847,912,954,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">ICZN</collectionCode>
(
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD08BF7DD0FEFD1C1" box="[927,987,954,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1999.0">1999</number>
, Article 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD72FF7DD0845D1C1" box="[1083,1137,954,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="34.2">34.2</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Both names are available and deemed to be of subspecific rank according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFF8FFEFD1C9F7B9085FD1E5" author="ICZN" box="[733,1131,989,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode id="ED440AF8FFF8FFEFD1C9F7B90F2BD1E5" box="[733,799,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">ICZN</collectionCode>
(
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD03BF7B90F5FD1E5" box="[815,875,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1999.0">1999</number>
, Articles 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD0CCF7B9083FD1E5" box="[984,1035,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="10.2">10.2</number>
, 45.6.4)
</bibRefCitation>
. The depository of its 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD678F7B909A8D1E5" box="[1388,1436,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">type</typeStatus>
material has remained unknown so far. For 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD168F0660811D60A" box="[636,1061,1025,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="torridus" variety="moestissimus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD168F0660F6ED60A" box="[636,858,1025,1049]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD085F0650811D60A" box="[913,1061,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">moestissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, proposed for an uniformly black form lacking dorsal markings, a 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD114F0410E04D62D" box="[512,560,1062,1086]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">type</typeStatus>
locality (“Sta. 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD1C3F0420F72D62D" box="[727,838,1061,1086]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Mopaliidae" genus="Catharina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Catharina</taxonomicName>
” = Santa Catarina state of South 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD7A2F04208C8D62D" box="[1206,1276,1061,1086]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) was given. A single specimen from the same locality was located among unidentified specimens originating from Breddin’s collection deposited in the 
<collectionCode id="ED440AF8FFF8FFEFD2DAF0090E38D695" box="[462,524,1134,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">SDEI</collectionCode>
and designated as 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD1FEF00A0F61D695" box="[746,853,1133,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">lectotype</typeStatus>
. No 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD099F0090F89D695" box="[909,957,1134,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">type</typeStatus>
locality was specified for 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD7E5F0090D27D6BA" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="torridus" variety="laetissimus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD7E5F009095DD696" box="[1265,1385,1133,1157]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD383F0F60D27D6BA" box="[151,275,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">laetissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an uniformly “rusty yellow” (“rostgelb”) form with black markings at anterior and lateral margins and cicatrices of pronotum; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFF8FFEFD2B5F0D20E78D6DD" author="Breddin" box="[417,588,1205,1230]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Breddin, G. (1906) Rhynchotographische Beitrage. (Zweites Stuck.) Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 25 (5 - 7), 188 - 200." type="journal article" year="1906">
Breddin (
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD11EF0D20E70D6DD" box="[522,580,1205,1230]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1906.0">1906</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that it was distributed in South 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD0E3F0D20863D6DD" box="[1015,1111,1205,1230]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD78FF0D10937D6DD" box="[1179,1283,1206,1230]" name="Paraguay" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD632F0D209A3D6DD" box="[1318,1431,1205,1230]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, but he did not have specimens from Central 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD1BEF0BE0F3AD6E1" box="[682,782,1241,1266]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
. From among the 
<specimenCount id="9D5359B4FFF8FFEFD0FEF0BD08B3D6E1" box="[1002,1159,1241,1266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" type="generic">
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD0FEF0BD0832D6E1" box="[1002,1030,1242,1266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="80.0">80</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD7A0F0BD091AD6E2" box="[1204,1326,1241,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD7A0F0BD091AD6E2" box="[1204,1326,1241,1265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Breddin’s collection we selected for 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD125F09A0EA3D705" box="[561,663,1277,1302]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">lectotype</typeStatus>
the one that fits the original description the best.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFF8FFEFD3D3F1460ECBD7B6" blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
These varieties have not been treated subsequently by any authors except 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC4EFCCFFF8FFEFD716F1460883D729" author="Kirkaldy" box="[1026,1207,1313,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W. (1909) Catalogue of the Hemiptera (Heteroptera) with biological and anatomical references, lists of foodplants and parasites, etc. Vol. I. Cimicidae. F. L. Dames, Berlin, xl + 392 pp." type="book" year="1909">
Kirkaldy (
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD761F145089BD729" box="[1141,1199,1314,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1909.0">1909</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who placed them as varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD20FF1210E77D74D" authority="Burmeister, 1835" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[283,579,1349,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD20FF1210D1DD74E" box="[283,297,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD223F1220D43D74E" box="[311,375,1349,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">klugii</emphasis>
Burmeister, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD11CF1220E77D74D" box="[520,579,1349,1374]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1835.0">1835</number>
</taxonomicName>
. The distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD033F1210FB7D74E" box="[807,899,1349,1373]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD033F1210F01D74E" box="[807,821,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD057F1220FB7D74E" box="[835,899,1349,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD724F12208B2D74D" box="[1072,1158,1349,1374]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and, to a limited degree, some countries south of 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD2D6F10E0E23D791" box="[450,535,1385,1410]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Mexico</collectingCountry>
in Central 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD1BCF10E0F38D791" box="[680,780,1385,1410]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
. Because the two varieties were described from South 
<collectingCountry id="F342D2ADFFF8FFEFD383F1EA0CCED7B5" box="[151,250,1421,1446]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
, Kirkaldy’s (
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD29EF1E90DF1D7B5" box="[394,453,1422,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1909.0">1909</number>
) action was clearly in error.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFF8FFEFD3D3F1D60E82D425" blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD3D3F1D60D93D7DA" box="[199,423,1457,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD3D3F1D60D93D7DA" box="[199,423,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a highly polychromatic species; the 
<typeStatus id="54EE2C9FFFF8FFEFD076F1D60FE0D7D9" box="[866,980,1457,1482]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">lectotypes</typeStatus>
of both varieties are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD693F1D50CC5D7FE" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD693F1D50CC5D7FE" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and do not merit recognition even at subspecies level, therefore we recognize them as 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD600F1B20DBAD401" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">new junior subjective synonyms</emphasis>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD2A3F19D0E1AD402" box="[439,558,1529,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD2A3F19D0E1AD402" box="[439,558,1529,1553]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A photo of another common variety and a brief review of the bionomics of this species were provided by Eger 
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD131F2790E69D426" box="[549,605,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD178F27A0E9DD425" box="[620,681,1565,1590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="2015.0">2015</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA923DFFF8FFEFD3D3F2260880D449" blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" box="[199,1204,1601,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD3D3F2260D48D449" bold="true" box="[199,380,1601,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Current status.</emphasis>
New junior subjective synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="4C55E9BEFFF8FFEFD00CF2260884D449" authority="Scopoli, 1772" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[792,1200,1601,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis id="B9214E2FFFF8FFEFD00CF2260FC3D44A" box="[792,1015,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
(Scopoli, 
<number id="3D9D801AFFF8FFEFD77FF2250893D449" box="[1131,1191,1602,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1772.0">1772</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
